glosses.gloss: A large class of sedentary marine coelenterates that includes sea anemones and corals; the medusoid phase is entirely suppressed

Actinozoa is an obsolescent term in systematic zoology, first used by Henri Marie Ducrotay de Blainville in his Manuel d'Actinologie to designate animals the organs of which were disposed radially about a centre.
Anthozoa is a class of marine invertebrates which includes the sea anemones, stony corals, soft corals and gorgonians.
